                <div style="background: #e8f5e9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #8B5CF6;">
                    <strong>üí° Local Insider Tips:</strong>
                    <ul style="margin-top: 10px; color: #6B7280; line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li>Book the sunset timing ‚Äì it's truly magical and perfect for photos!</li>
                        <li>Sit back when the camel stands up; lean forward when it sits down</li>
                        <li>Hold onto the saddle handle ‚Äì it's a unique swaying motion!</li>
                        <li>Arrive 10 minutes early to meet your camel and get comfortable</li>
                        <li>Ask your guide to take photos from different angles ‚Äì they know the best shots!</li>
                        <li>The BBQ dinner is generous ‚Äì come hungry!</li>
                        <li>Dress modestly to respect local culture (no shorts or sleeveless tops preferred)</li>
                        <li>Camels sometimes make funny sounds ‚Äì it's normal, they're just communicating!</li>
                    </ul>
