                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Camel Rides in Agadir</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        How long does the sunset camel ride experience last?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The complete <strong>sunset camel ride Agadir</strong> experience lasts approximately 4-5 hours total, including hotel pickup and drop-off. The actual camel ride along the beach is about 1 hour during sunset, followed by 1.5-2 hours for the mint tea ceremony, BBQ dinner, and entertainment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Is the camel ride suitable for children and families?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Absolutely! Our <strong>camel ride in Agadir</strong> is perfect for families. Children as young as 3-4 years old can participate (riding with a parent), while older children can ride independently. Our camels are gentle and well-trained, and our experienced handlers ensure everyone's safety and comfort. It's an adventure kids will remember forever!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Do I need any riding experience for the camel ride?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>No experience necessary! Our <strong>Agadir camel riding tour</strong> is designed for first-timers. The camel handlers will assist you with mounting and dismounting, explain basic riding techniques, and walk alongside you throughout the ride. Camels have a natural, gentle rhythm that's easy to adjust to. Within minutes, you'll feel comfortable!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        What should I wear for the camel ride?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>For your <strong>camel ride on the beach Agadir</strong>, wear comfortable, loose-fitting pants or a long skirt (easier for mounting), closed-toe shoes or sandals with straps, and modest clothing that covers shoulders. Bring a light jacket for evening, sunglasses, and a hat. Avoid shorts and sleeveless tops out of respect for local culture.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Are the camels well-treated and safe?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Absolutely! Animal welfare is our top priority. Our camels are well-cared for, healthy, regularly vet-checked, and work limited hours with plenty of rest. They're fed quality diets, have shelter from heat, and are treated with respect. Our camels are calm, well-trained, and comfortable carrying riders. We never overwork our animals.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        What's included in the BBQ dinner?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>The <strong>camel ride and BBQ Agadir</strong> dinner includes grilled meats (chicken, beef, or lamb), traditional Moroccan salads, fresh bread, seasonal fruits, and refreshing beverages. Vegetarian options are available with advance notice. The meal is freshly prepared on-site and served in a traditional Berber tent atmosphere with live entertainment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Is the camel ride scary or uncomfortable?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Not at all! While mounting and dismounting can feel unusual at first (the camel rocks forward and back), it's perfectly safe and our handlers guide you through it. Once you're settled, the ride is smooth and relaxing. The gentle swaying motion is actually quite peaceful. Most first-timers are surprised by how comfortable and enjoyable it is!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        What time does the camel ride start?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Pickup times vary by season to ensure perfect sunset timing. In summer (June-Aug), pickup is around 5:00-5:30 PM. In winter (Dec-Feb), it's earlier at 4:00-4:30 PM. Spring and fall pickups are around 4:30-5:00 PM. We'll confirm your exact pickup time when you book, ensuring you experience the magical sunset perfectly timed!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question">
                        Can I do the camel ride if I'm pregnant or have back problems?
                        <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Pregnant women and people with back or joint problems should consult their doctor before booking. The mounting/dismounting motion and gentle swaying may not be suitable for everyone. If you have concerns, please contact us ‚Äì we can discuss your specific situation and provide honest advice about whether this tour is right for you.</p>
                    </div>
